JOHANNESBURG - Lynne Brown’s spokesperson has refused to comment on allegations the public enterprises minister’s partner scored major oil tenders from Eskom.
	
	The Sunday Times Newspaper alleges that E Smart Solutions, which is owned by Brown's partner Ingrid Tufvesson, scored two tenders worth R1.2-million. READ: Brown asks PA to resign over Gupta links That's despite not having any expertise in the industry. It also alleges that Brown's former PA’s sister is one of the directors. The paper further alleges, the first of the contracts was awarded shortly after the appointment of Matshela Koko as acting CEO in January. eNCA